#HappyBlackHistoryMonth 🌱 Being on the front lines preparing Gen Z for life on post covid earth and arming them with the environmental tools we need to succeed and sustain>>>>>> 
I appreciate Coach Hankerson for reaching out to me and asking me to shine light on the importance of opening your mind to pursue sustainable career paths with the students at Rickards High School , shoutout to @rickardsenviro 🌍! This was a very captivating experience and I know there is someone in one of those classes that’s going to change the world. Y’all this is no joke. The future is now and WE will be facing the horrific realities inflicted upon us by negligent generations before us and capitalism. Climate Chaos effects us all but it disproportionately effects BLACK AND BROWN communities. Environmental Racism is REAL. Rickards High School is located in a food desert. Jackson,Mississippi does not have clean water. Ohio has hydrochloric acid raining from the sky. Florida is losing keystone species that keep the ENTIRE ocean clean. THIS IS NOT A DRILL. Ignoring this won’t make it go away. Follow @sustainfamu for real time environmental updates on job, scholarship, career and volunteer opportunities! We are in this TOGETHER. Monday, God used me in ways that only He deserves credit for. By His grace, I was able to visit this STEAM Elementary School in Atlanta, Georgia and teach these beautiful future scientists and leaders about the importance of caring for Earth and how to nurture her by learning how to garden & care for plants. We are one with nature. I packed up my prius with my @sustainfamu Travel Science  Lab🧪 and we conducted super fun experiments just like the ones we do in our real lab @famuenvironmental . Huge expression of gratitude to @wynuworldwide for sponsoring the soil, pots and individual science kits that I was able to put together for each student for them to take home so they can remember this day forever, the day they became a Scientist 👩🏾‍🔬. Our babies are the ones who will be inhabiting the world capitalism is destroying so I will continue to be obedient to one of my many missions here while I am here. I have to Fuel The Future and I will continue to do so Day By Day BUT I CAN NOT AND WILL NOT DO IT ALONE…..Soooo click the link in my bio and GO STREAM DAY BY DAY😇 Music is my main mission, Science is one of my many side quest but all of my side quest lead back to the main mission🫡. Trust the process & tap in now…God and I have a lot in store. #OneRattlerCouldChangeTheWorld  shirt from @hbcucrwns

This experience was absolutely amazing. Huge thank you again to Odyssey for inviting me to Help your 8th graders answer the question: "How do I become my own boss?". I had so much fun connecting with the students, listening to their amazing entrepreneurial endeavors and sharing my professional feedback. Each student was SO BRIGHT & had such unique, awesome and beautiful career paths. Ownership is so important, definitely as a musician, which is why I co- founded my production company @wynuworldwide with @phenaego ! All of my music is released & registered through @wynuworldwide . I was so blessed to share my personal insight about my growing journey as a musical artist and buisness owner along side another buisness owner I deeply respect, @saimakesbeats . It was so alchemical to be received so deeply by the students and to remind them that all they admire about me, is a reflection of the best parts within them. Confidence is truly key & there’s nothing that was more fulfilling than watching the confidence of these young minds grow as we exchanged energy. Creatives, artist and musicians RUN THE WORLD 🚀. I can’t wait to see how each of these bright beings shake the world with their necessary energy. I will be back. ❤️ #Motion #StreamMotionMantra

What an absolute honor to share with you all that I am one of the recipients of the Congressional Black Caucus Young, Gifted and Green 40 Under 40 Award presented by @blackmillennials4flint during @congressionalblackcaucus ALC. #YoungGiftedGreen 40 under 40 is an annual list of Black, Latinx (non-white presenting) and Indigenous environmental justice leaders under the age of 40 from across the U.S. who are grappling with complex solutions to solve the Climate Crisis and dismantle Environmental Racism.
I was nominated because of my research as a @noaa CCME scholar at @famu_1887 , my work with sustainability at FAMU @famuenvironmental @nexusenergywaterfood (@sustainfamu ) , my feature on @msnbc and ABC 27 with @trymaine.lee , my STEAM work with youth in Atlanta & my local Tallahassee Community, and my commitment to sustainable fashion in my partnership with @goodwillbigbend @goodwillintl ♻️. The keynote speaker will be State Rep. @justinjpearson . I am so blessed to be on this list, God is really working.This time next week I’ll be on stage accepting my award and giving my speech 🌱👩🏾‍🔬🧪🧬🧡💚

In two days I accept my 40 under 40 Young Gifted and Green award in Washington, D.C presented by @blackmillennials4flint during @congressionalblackcaucus . I think it finally hit me today that they picked the perfect person for this award because that is literally me😭 The lemon- lime grape fruits are blooming in our @sustainfamu SEED garden and while watering them, I was like wow….What you water WILL grow and the fruits of your labor are REAL🌱 This award is a mere fruit of God’s labor through me and this is only the beginning! Blessed is an understatement. Glory be to God FRFR🍈🌱. Don’t forget to stream Motion Mantra ✨

We have PAID RESEARCH and SCHOLARSHIP opportunities available at the School Of The Environment! I have been taking it Day By Day & I am excited to announce my partnership with the School Of The Environment to change the lives of 70 future scholars! 💚🌱🧡 Please help me in this endeavor to ensure that our people have equal opportunity to explore these spaces! 
Send this video to anyone who: 
1. Would appreciate a PAID OPPORTUNITY in a SUSTAINABLE career. 
2. Is in High School and would possibly pursue a sustainable career if given the opportunity (this is the opportunity)
3. Someone who is affected by CLIMATE CHAOS (we all are) 
4. A future or current HBCU attendee! 
You can contact us via email DM @sustainfamu ! Over the next few weeks, I will be showing you guys what we do at The School Of The Environment first hand!🌱 Save and share this post. Let’s take this Day By Day change 70 lives together! #Day1

The School Of The Environment is a progressive, productive and proactive safe space. FAMU is located in a Food Desert which not only directly affects the physical health of our community but it also takes a huge tole on our mental health! Gardening aids in targeting the healing of both. Gardening has been shown to lighten moods and lower levels of stress and anxiety. It’s very gratifying to plant, tend, harvest and share your own food. Routines provide structure to our day and are linked to improved mental health. Gardening routines, like watering and weeding, can create a soothing rhythm to ease stress! We have 70 slots available at SOE🌱 You don’t have to be an expert, you just have to be human🫶🏾 Join us today! #DayByDay
